<section xml:id="EvalFunc" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Evaluating Functions</title>
    <p>
        In this section, we will use function notation to evaluate functions. We will also learn how to interpret 
        the meaning of the inputs and outputs of a function.
    </p>

<video label="Meaning-of-Inputs-Outputs" source="Meaning-of-Inputs-Outputs.mp4"/>

      <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Complete the input/output table for the equation <m>y = 2(x + 3)</m>. Be sure to simplify your answer.
            </p>
            <table>
                <title>Input/Output Table for <m>y = 2(x+3)</m></title>
                <tabular>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Input</cell>
                        <cell>Output</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>-1</m></cell>
                        <cell>ans1</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>0</m></cell>
                        <cell>ans2</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                        <cell>ans3</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
</section>